hints.content:
We can think of division as the following: 

$\begin{align}
\greenD{\text{ Total}}\div\blueD{\text{ Number of groups}}=\purpleC{\text{ Size of the groups}}\\\\
\greenD{\text{ Total}}\div\purpleC{\text{ Size of the groups}}=\blueD{\text{ Number of groups}}
\end{align}$

Let's put those numbers in the equation.

$\begin{align}
\greenD{\text{ Total}}\div\blueD{\text{ Number of groups}}&=\purpleC{\text{ Size of the groups}}\\\\
\greenD{20}\div\blueD{4}&=\purpleC{\text{ Size of the groups}}
\end{align}$
